# OpenRouter Skill Routing

- Treat [AGENTS.md](../../AGENTS.md) as the repository-level workflow baseline.
- Load the canonical skill under `skills/<name>/SKILL.md` before using any wrapper in `.cursor/skills/<name>/`.
- For bounded local coding edits, use `ollama-worker` from `C:\vscode\SharedOllama` when available.
- Use `openrouter-heavy-task-gate` to choose between local `ollama-worker` and OpenRouter escalation.
- Use `openrouter-glm52` for heavy coding analysis, cross-file reasoning, long-context work, and second-pass review.
- Use `openrouter-model-advisor` only when model selection materially affects cost, latency, modality, or quality.
- Use `openrouter-pdf-extract` for PDF extraction tasks.
- Prefer `openrouter-flux2-pro` for FLUX.2 Pro image work.
- Keep OpenRouter prompts focused and secret-free, and validate any code changes locally after model guidance.
